Moved avatar cache clearing to didFinishLaunchingWithOptions

The changes do not take immediate effect when doing this in applicationDidBecomeActive, because already cached gravatars on existing user object instances are not purged. This makes it more intuitive.

Load cached gravatar via NSData. Closes #347

The problem was a race condition that occured while loading the cached gravatar while at the same time the avatar cache got cleared. UIImage. imageWithData loads the image as a valid image (instead of returning nil) in case it can read the header. The image data was corrupted when the image got deleted while loading it, that's why only a black gravatar was shown.

For more details, see this answer on SO:
http://stackoverflow.com/a/10685962/183537

Deactivated NSURLCache and remove cachePolicy code

NSURLCache seems to have a problem with Cache-Control="private" headers. Most resources of GitHubs API use this header and the response gets cached longer than the interval given by GitHub (in most cases 60 seconds). This way we lose caching, but its still better than unexpected results.

Section the accounts table view by endpoint

These sections make it easy to see which logins belong
to which github endpoints. It is not uncommon for someone
to have the same login on github.com as they do on an
enterprise github installation. Fixed a problem in
this situation where the sliding view would show data for
the first account listed if it had the same login as
the selected account. Also cleared out the user and
organization caches when the account is changed.

Disable scroll-to-top for menu. Closes #186

Scroll-to-top does not work in case there are multiple view controllers - for us this is the case when the user is signed in and the menu is shown besides (or below) the main view controller.

From the Apple docs:
This gesture works on a single visible scroll view; if there are multiple scroll views (for example, a date picker) with this property set, or if the delegate returns NO in scrollViewShouldScrollToTop:, UIScrollView ignores the request.
